<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4298245>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 51. Georeferenced collection records of Lasioglossum (D.) kunzei (Cockerell, 1898) (vermilion squares), L. (D.) semibrunneum (Cockerell, 1895) (blue-green squares) and intermediate specimens of uncertain identity (yellow squares) as well as predicted distribution by maximum entropy ecological niche modeling in Maxent (colour shading). Warmer colours indicate higher cloglog probability of occurrence. Maxent analysis was run separately for L. (D.) kunzei (left) and L. (D.) semibrunneum (right), but all georeferenced records for both species are shown on both maps to highlight distributional differences. Lasioglossum (D.) kunzei and L. (D.) semibrunneum have largely non-overlapping distributions, but are predicted to intermix in northern Utah, southern Arizona/northern Sonora, and northern Nevada (although no L. (D.) semibrunneum records are known from Nevada)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4298245/files/figure.png" .

